\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 the people}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6975372\charrsid11093751 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 s houses automatically.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 This is what made life tick more then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Well I think so, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 You mentioned your mother had friends - what about your father, did he have many friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Where would he have seen them - he used to go out you\rquote re your mother's brother on Saturday night didn't he?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Yes. No he was the - he was the husband of my father's sister. They - they were brothers-in-law you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Would you say they shared the same friends mainly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh pretty well I think, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Friends were invited into the home quite a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 And they'd be offered something to eat and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Yes. Took your turn - it went round the family you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did people call in casually without invitations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh very often - very often, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 And your parents went out visiting friends and neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What do you think your parents did when they got together with their friends and neighbours - would they have made music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 This was quite a common thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Yes. Nearly everybody had a piano - at one particular place, this uncle Jim's, they had - 'course 
he'd - he was one of the few people as had got a phonograph in those days and there was another thing, they used to call it a planchette I believe it's called. You put your hand on it and it makes all kinds of designs and - it was after the style of readi
ng you hand, some people could read all kinds of thing into these designs, you follow what I mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 They did this quite a bit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 So you'd be playing games and things like that as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 That's the idea, yes. They were very - very simple games kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
Many people divide society into different social classes or groups, in that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one and some t another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Can you tell me some of the different ones - what you thought they were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Well I found the - what - the ordinary person was called the la-di-dah - pretty well off type.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What social class would you have called them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 The - professional and semi-professional the classes. And we had such a
 lot around us but there was a very sharp line drawn. Oh I found it so, yes. They would - don't want to be bothered with you kind of thing and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 You were conscious of this as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 As a child even, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Which class or group would you say you belonged to yourself in that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 In that - I belonged to the working class group.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What sort of people belonged to the same working class group as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Practically everybody in the area that - there were - the bulk of the people, I'll say my }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12391602\charrsid11093751 own}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
 street for instance. They were all a tradesman and I'll certainly say that seventy-five per cent worked for the Dock Board - they see - the men used to go to work together, come home together and they had everything in common.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What sort of people belonged to the professional and semi-professional group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 There was parsons - let me see - business people out of the town. You see we were very sharply divided in - just where I lived in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}South Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. The backs of - of large houses in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12391602\charrsid11093751 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Devonshire}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} came in - into {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}
South Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12391602\charrsid11093751 The staffs, for instance, was not allowed to use the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Devonshire Road
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 If you worked in a house you didn't come in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Devonshire Road{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} way. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12391602\charrsid11093751 Oh no}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 , you had to use the back door in - by {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}South Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, walk up along garden. Oh yes. And when you went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Princes{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Park{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} you'd see them maids coming in the back door from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Princes{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Park{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Buy the - the people concerned came in the - carriage and pairs, coaches, hansoms down {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}
Devonshire Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12391602\charrsid11093751 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Belvedere}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} the same thing would apply. And go in the front way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 With - with cert - you were pretty well taught at school that people that were above your rank - professional and
 semi-professional and so on and - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6975372\charrsid11093751 big}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  business people, that you always called them Sir or Madam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 This was expressed in school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh definitely, yes. As I say, you used to repeat perhaps - I don't know where it's from now - to lower my 
head lowly and reverently toward my betters - and you were told these people were your betters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What did your parents say about this sort of thing - did they repeat this to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Well they'd been brought up to the same thing. For instance, when w
e went in the Army and officer in the Army - well - you - you done the same thing there. You didn't lower your head lowly and reverently but you - but you saluted him and you called him sir and - like he - they - some of them were very conscious of the - 
the fact that they were a - they really thought that they were a superior being to you. It had been instilled into them. The same as it had been instilled into us that we were inferior to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did you personally feel that you were inferior?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Over
 a lot of things, yes, over a lot of things, yes. And I found it at school. I had - labour - just - just - just to mention one for - a chap I used to sit with in school, he's - he was James Laver. He's now - he's now the curator of the 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}Victoria{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Albert{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
PlaceName}}Museum{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 he's a leading authority in the country on period dress, all these film companies consult him. He was an ordinary church school boy and sat next to me in school. So - on top of him, the headmaster's son went to school - was in the same class }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6975372\charrsid11093751 as}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  me. Now those boys - I'm not conning - they were treated as very superior people. In the class - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Treated very differently from the rest of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12391602\charrsid11093751 Definitely}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Were you ever told to touch your cap and show respect in certain ways - you told me you were expected to say sir and madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh yes, you were expected to, yes. To be subservient to these betters.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 And you were expected to call them sir, master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Sir, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Who would you have particularly have referred to as Master or Madam - would you have ever used this sort of expression to anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
Well - a parson - well, you wouldn't say master, you would call him sir you see. Any boss in the office - I - I went to work for a steamship company and - all the 
senior clerks you would address as sir, you'd be told to address them as sir. I have rows here - the kiddies call their mother Rosa. They call their dad Reg. I wouldn't stand for that. They started to - call me different things - I said if you can't call 
me grandad, go, get out. It's always been instilled into me. Oh yes. Mind you, I get the same over Margaret's kids. I told them upteen times. Well you know }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12391602\charrsid11093751 dad}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 , she said, things are different now. I said, well that's all right, you might think so - wouldn't
 see me - I said, you always called me dad, don't you? I said, what did you call your mother? Mum. I said, well there you are. I said, you wouldn't think to call me Jim or your mother Ann. I don't like it myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 In the district where you lived when you were a child who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
You speaking when I was a kiddie? Who was the most important people. Well the Vicar. The schoolmaster - school head and - the doctor. Any professional man like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Why do you think they were considered important - as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Well first of all a doctor used to affect a tall hat. So did the - it wasn't the Vicar it was a Canon in our case - Cannon Woodward.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What sort of hat would he have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12391602\charrsid11093751 A tall hat. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 So he would be different immediately because of his dress you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
Oh yes - a tall hat and a frock coat I mean. I should say a tall hat and a frock coat was the - that - that was the uniform of your betters kind of business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Who would their friends have been - who would the clergy have associated with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 I suppose the - they mucked in together pretty well. All the - all the upper classes - people -l all the big - all the big cheeses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Would you have put teachers in this class - who would they have associated with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Well whilst you call - while you call it - whilst you paid homage to your teachers I think it was more in fear than -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 You didn't feel they were quite in this sort of bracket?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 No. Since I've appreciated my teachers 
very much since I've left school - I mean were they called you by your surname at school. After I left school my teachers used to call me by my - by my }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12391602\charrsid11093751 Christian}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  name and - there's a couple I've gone and had drinks with and been treated as a - quite an equal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 This is since you've been older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 But as a child was the teacher as important a person as the clergyman or the doctor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Very autocratic. He was very - a teacher was very autocratic. And - they were certainly very - very fond of
 the cane and the pointer and all that kind of thing. Yes - very keen on discipline. Now - in our standard two in the room was a series of steps - just ordinary steps, you know, wooden steps. And you sat on one step and - with a slate and a slate pencil. 
A
s the teacher wrote say the alphabet on the blackboard or numbers on the blackboard you carefully copied these down on your slate. The children down below like you could push them in the neck with the point of your pencil and do all this sort of thing and
 
of course if you get caught doing that you'd get a fourpenny one on the-ear hole and mark somebody down and whatever your trouble you'd bring two or three others down. But - different to the present day. Another point I'd like to make clear, when - when m
y family were young -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 No, when my family - I followed out the routine of my people. There was always a cane hanging on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12391602\charrsid11093751 mantelpiece}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  over the corner of a picture. I'm not saying it was used very often. Only if you done something 
seriously wrong. Oh it was there to be seen and to be felt if the occasion demanded it and there was no such thing as just a threat - you - you got it at once. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12391602\charrsid11093751 Even}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  if they - didn't mean to hit you with it - you know, make a swipe with it and hit - hit the table and put the wind up you kind of business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 So you carried on what your parents had done for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Who would the employers friends have been do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Well I - I found it was - they stuck together as a solid - they stuck together as a solid block, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What sort of people would you say went to the church you attended - the mission in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Shopkeepers in the main.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Was this the mission?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 No, this was - this was church at night. The Church of Engl
and or the - I - I used to go Church of England one Sunday, got to a Wesleyan the Sunday because my parents had belonged to both although I think they were inclined to be more Wesleyan than anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 These would be mainly shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Mainly shopkeepers, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What about the people who went to chapel - what kind of people would have gone to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Well - it was a Wesleyan chapel. That was a - that's part of the church you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What sort of people would have gone to St Silas' church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 The same thing. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Was there any friction as far as you know between Catholics and Protestants when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh yes, very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Can you recall anything about that at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh yes, we used to go to Mount Carmel school only a couple of hundred yards away and attack the kids.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 You did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
Yes. It was a - a tradition. Oh yes. Have - even going along the street on the appointed days on the twelfth of July, that was - Orange Day and - oh pinch these k
ids hats or pull their hats down - pull their coats off and all that. We'd attack them and on their particular day they could get hold of you they'd attack you. But it was - on say Orangeman's Day on the twelfth of July - I could tell you the streets ther
e
 which the Orange Lodges used to have to pass by - police doing - and the police 'd be drawn and stop 'em going into certain quarters - the police 'd be drawn, with their truncheons - I've seen windows open and buckets of water poured onto the Orange Lodg
es have gone passed. It was something that was - I was a boy - it was something that was done in those days that isn't done so much now but in that particular part of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Liverpool{\*\xmlclose}
 there's still a considerable amount of feeling Oh yes. I have - for instance, I 
worked at Roderick Bank it's a large destructor, stables and corporation yard. One of my carters there, a chap named Weaver, he's a very - he isn't big - but he's a very arrogant Protestant. And they'd been on a church parade one Sunday morning, you know,
 working out at this place, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Thornton Place{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 and they'd been for a march round to church and come back and - there were - he was somewhat late in getting dismissed and all this and - it was early closing time at the pub that he went to. And he - he went into 
this place with all his regalia on and he said - make way for the pride of Toxworth. Make way for the Pride of Toxworth, he said as he goes in 'cos he wanted a drink quick and someone made way for him. They just picked him off the floor and carried him ho
me. This is the Catholic pub he went into - a place well known. Red Nolans - this chap is an Orangeman himself - and over the weekend he's got a great }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12391602\charrsid11093751 influx}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  of Catholics from other pubs he'd had that come round to see him on a Sunday and he happened to fall in one of these - he just picked the wrong pub on the wrong morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 You were saying you were doing all these things yet you married a Catholic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 When you discovered she was a Catholic what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Didn't make any difference. 
No. I'd come to an age of my own understanding. I'd - I'd prev - I'd - prior to this I'd done five years in the Army - five years in the war. It'd given me a totally different outlook on - religious life and all what it meant and all that kind of thing an
d I'd had very - some very good friends that were Catholics and some very good friends that were Prods and I never differentiated.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 We were going to talk about the different standards of living of the working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 You said there were different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Can you describe a family in a group - to give the different standards in a working class group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Well - the best way I can do that is to say that - a very personal friend of mine he was a manager of what was known as 
the T.S.B. Stores in Mill Street. And - people really used to come in there and say a ha'porth of tea and a ha'porth of fourpenny. That was a ha'porth of fourpenny margarine - two ounces of margarine and tea was a penny an ounce. So they got half an ounce
 of - a - a penn'orth - a h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6975372\charrsid11093751 ap}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
'orth of tea and a ha'porth of fourpenny and a ha'porth of tea was tea sugar and milk. They put in say two spoonfuls of tea - four spoonfuls of sugar and a big spoonful of condensed milk. That was just screwed into a paper and g
iven to them for a ha'penny. Now you will hardly believe that but I can vouch for that and tell you where the shop was. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Mill Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, the corner of Rutter Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 This would be the very poor would it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 This was the very poor people. You see, a do
cker got about three and sixpence a day if he got a morning and afternoon's work. And if he - if there was no money in the house and he hadn't had any work well - there was no tea to be made that day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 So there were tremendously different standards within your own class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
Oh - it was terrible, yes. It's like the kiddies in the - the poorer people the police used to clothe the kiddies. The Police Aid Clothing Society otherwise the kids wouldn't have any clothes. And - an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12391602\charrsid11093751 enormous}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  number of children in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Liverpool{\*\xmlclose}
 never knew what a pair of boots were. Only when they got issued by the Police Aid Clothing Society. They had corduroy pants, a jersey and a pair of boots and stockings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Do you think that one group in the working class group felt itself su
perior to the rest in any way - were you aware of any people who felt themselves superior to other in your own sort of working class group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh yes. Yes. Specially amongst - people that would describe themselves I suppose as - shop managers or clerical workers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 They would feel they were superior?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Yes. The - the - the white collar - brigade you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 We are some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What would a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12391602\charrsid11093751 rough}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  family be to you as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Well I think where the parents were fond - fond of going out for a drink and all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6975372\charrsid11093751 that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  kind of thing and leaving the child to its own -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Sort of lack of caring?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Yes, that's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What about respectable - would you have put your own family in that group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 I would have said, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12391602\charrsid11093751 yes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 , yes. No, no, but we - we were disciplined to start with and - that you were - my grand - I was always taught at home to be respectable to older people and - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Do you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
Yes. Definitely. There definitely was, quite a large - you see, labourers by and large were far more casual in their work than were the tradesmen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 So the craftsmen definitely felt themselves superior?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
Oh yes, yes, yes. And a fellow was - as I say, as you see on the birth certificate it's got a journeyman carpenter or a journeyman shipwright - that's apart of an ordinary - shipwright.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 So this was a craftsman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh yes, yes. Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Yes, I think she felt she was on a social par with me dad you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 And your father felt he was working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
Not exactly - no, he thought - he thought he was working class but he thought he was better than the common or garden class - yes, he thought he was - superior to the common or garden labourer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 And your mother felt this because of your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Yes, I - I take it so. And her - her - her brothers were all tradesman as well you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another and can you remember anyone who did? Was this done a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
I don't know. I don't know what to - answer there. Very rarely because - all the friends and everything else, the - I think they very rarely moved from one class to the other, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What sort of people would have been referred to like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Possibly your schoolteacher or your Sunday school teacher and - different shopkeepers I've heard described as a real -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What would they have to be like to be described as a real lady or a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 They - they were people that could adapt themselves to the circumstances. I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 This is what your definition would have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Do you remember seeing a policeman }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12391602\charrsid11093751 around}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh yes, always. The police was round every hour, you could tell the time by the policemen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What did you think of the policemen as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 I thought - I thought a lot of the policeman. He - he a
lways moved you off if you gathered round a street corner you always had to - get out of the road when - when he hove in sight and he just - policemen always carried the gloves in his hand and he'd always - come on, get going - get moving or something lik
e that. Wouldn't hurt you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 But his presence was enough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh yes. Yes, his very presence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 How do you think he treated people generally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 A policeman? I think very good. I - I've - I've always been brought up to have not from a - a sense o
f fear but I've always been brought up to treat a policeman as a friend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did your mother ever say, I'll fetch the policeman if you're naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh - things like that, yes. I - either that or she'd put me in a bin cart or things like that - that was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Was your home rented when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Yes. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Yes. He -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh - you - you wouldn't see a landlord, you would see a landlord's agent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 How did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
Oh he was just a - he was like a white collar - worker as it were. He'd be - dressed up with a stiff collar and tie and - carry a brolly on his arm. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6975372\charrsid11093751 It}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  was a kind of a - rank of authority you know - was a brolly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ands meet at any time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 At times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What did you think about it as a child if you were aware that sometimes they had to struggle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12391602\charrsid11093751 Well you'd think it was very hard lines I suppose but - y
es - but - by and large mine didn't have to - my people didn't have to struggle but there were times when they - when you had to forgo this or that because - possibly }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6975372\charrsid11093751 you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12391602\charrsid11093751  - you'd just had a new suit or there'd been some other extra expense put on in some way or other, yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
Maybe a wedding or - something like that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Was your father ever ill and if he was did it make any difference to you and the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Well - my father wasn't ill until the end of his days when he had the accident.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 So he was a fairly healthy man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh yes. Yes. As I say, he was an athlete. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did you ever get help from the guardians or the parish or any charity at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 When there was someone in the district where you lived as a child whom the 
