\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3695530\charrsid11093751 How did you feel about the work, did you like it or dislike it?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh I liked it - oh I liked it, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did the job alter your attitude to school in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 No. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3695530\charrsid11093751 
I - I was finished by eight and - I could go home, have me breakfast, because when you firs
t went out you never kind of - dolled up at all, you just had a - a quick sluice - you put a - I always wore a - a ganzie with a - with a collar on and a tie and - like it was always worn if it was a wet day, wet morning, well obviously you'd put your ove
rcoat on.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 These were the only two part time jobs you did before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What did you do for your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 I went as an office boy. To the Harrison Line.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 How did you get that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Well - I - I th
ink I told you about - oh, I see. Oh I thought it was. Well - on the advice of the manager of the firm - on the advice of Colonel Bulman, who was one of the - one of the directors of the firm - he suggested that as a departure from the old and ancient cus
tom of - taking the boys from the Liverpool Collegiate etc. he - yes, well he suggested they should have - a small examination. Only a viva voca and - put the questions to the boys. There were four boys - three were from - high grade schools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 You said 
that this Colonel Bowman had an idea there were boys in the Elementary schools with just as high intelligence and he wanted to prove this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Yes. That - that - that was the point that he tried to make to the - to the other the directors. He later on to
ld me this. He - I didn't know anything at the time. Didn't know where the boys were from but - by their clothing and - general mannerisms they were of a - a higher grade type of boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 And you were given questions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Yes, we were given questions an
d - well - it was - despite the fact that I say so he said it was outstanding and he - you couldn't fail but notice it. And they were boys of two - they were your elders by two years. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 They were round about sixteen and you were fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 That's correct, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What exactly did you have to do in this job when you got it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Well first of all I was just an office boy deliver}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6975372\charrsid11093751 er}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  - your first job of the morning when you came, there were about six boys, we - we opened all the mail and th
en the senior boy allocated the letter which he just, you know, quickly glanced through to the different departments concerned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 And then what would you do after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 And then - well different - you were kind of allocated to different department
s - the customs, the - the - the freight, the cash and so on, different departments in the office, the boys were more or less allocated to - one boy to each department as it were. And you were a general - you know, general run about for them. You'd - you 
would take out mail, you would pick up mail and so on.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What hours did you work in this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 The hours then were eight thirty to five thirty. That was when I first started.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 And Sunday you wouldn't work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh Sunday was off, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What about Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Saturday under normal circumstances you finished at one. On a Saturday. But - i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6975372\charrsid11093751 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  there was a sailing on the Saturday - certain people would be required to stay. You would be staying - copying out consul invoices and bills of lading 
on a graph, you know the thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Things that wouldn't wait - that had to be}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16450927\charrsid11093751  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 That's right yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3695530\charrsid11093751 
And then we - I was - if I was on duty that day there was a ship sailing there would always be some last minute mail to catch the ship and - we us
ed to take that down to the Pierhead where a tug had been chartered and they used to pick up the ship in the river and the mail'd be transferred aboard. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
Couple of, you know, bags of it. That was - not - not - not G.P.O. mail.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 This was a direct thing from the office?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 From - yes, from - stuff that - you know, last minute stuff for the ship. Stuff for the skipper, stuff for the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3695530\charrsid11093751 purser}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  and - you know, what have you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did you get a half day in the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 A half day, yes, the Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Apart from Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh no, no, you didn't get any other time off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did you have any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh yes. I think - when I first started it was a week. And - people with - years of service, I don't know how many years, somewhere about t
en, then you - then you went onto a fortnight's leave.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 This was unusually really to get holidays with pay wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh - only for office workers in the main. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What were you paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Three and sixpence to start with. And - and dinners. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3695530\charrsid11093751 
You got a dinner voucher and you went to - in my case - a caf\'e9
 in South Castle Street - it was a well known place - Shearson's where the - the boss of the place, he wore - he wore a chef's hat and a white - gown kind of things, I don't know what you call it, dress - you know, overall. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 And - the joints would be in the window - there'd be lamb - beef, pork and like whatever was on the menu and he used to do all the slicing in - for people outsiders to see him doing it through the window as well to bring th
e people in you see. It was - well it was really appetising to see him performing on a joint and cutting it off. And hen that was just taken inside and - by the waitresses, like a waitresses on plates for the people that, you know, as they ordered it. But
 he - appeared to be carving the whole time and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did you feel that was a f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6975372\charrsid11093751 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 ir wage or not at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 At that time yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did you give any of this money to your mother?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 I turned it all in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 And how would she have spent it - in with her housekeeping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Would she give any back to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Well - actually it wasn't my mother you see, my mother was dead by then. Yes. So I - I - I handed it over to me dad. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Would he have given you any back as pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 I - I'd - I'd had me pocket money increased to sixpence a week. In addition to that I got tenpence which paid my fare to town and back.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 That's all you had - sixpence?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Sixpence pocket money and I used - before I was - well by the time I 
was fifteen I was taking a girl to a theatre on a Saturday night for that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 How did you get on with the other people you worked with - there were a lot of other office boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh fine. Fine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Very goo
d indeed. I even got in a private office with the boss. Miss Olive Bowman, she's just died now and left - a fabulous sum of money - and at that time she was being - despite the fact that she was as a - they were Protestants - a great Protestant family - s
he finished her education in Belgium. Yes. In a convent in Belgium, I don't know why but - I suppose there must have been - something about it - yes. And - I'd - by that time I'd graduated into the private office with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3695530\charrsid11093751 Colonel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  Bowman, I - I was his - chief }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3695530\charrsid11093751 fetcher}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  and carrier. Watched nobody pinched his cigars and things. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 So you obviously got into it very well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16450927\charrsid11093751 
And - but - but he used to send me to meet Miss Olive at Lime Street station and get a cab and I used to take her home to Bulwar
d Park and the other little private job I always had - was to - I used to get the money from our cashier an a - a Friday morning and take the wages out to Bulward Park to pay the staff.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 So they trusted you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Well it was mainly - the cashier made 
them into envelops but I always took them and this - and - I used to see Miss Olive or - it was Mrs Bowman to start with then when she passed on it became Miss Olive Bowman. And - I used to - be there. And they - they done just the same as us. As - as you
 got your wages packet so you signed on the appropriate line.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did you like or dislike this work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh I liked it. I did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did it alter your attitude to school in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 How long were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 From this -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What year would that have been when you started?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
I started in December 1912. And - I didn't go - on the sixth of August 1914 instead of going to work I went and joined the Army. Yes. I was fifteen years of age. But I was very big you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did your parents know about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh me father played - played Hamlet you see when I got home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 When you'd done it you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 You didn't tell him before you went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh no. I went - I was going to work and I found out that - that the Territorials had been - had been mobilized - I met a}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10490510\charrsid11093751  couple}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  of my mates who were reporting to tramway Road depot and I went down to Tramway Road and - and enlisted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 And your father raised }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10490510\charrsid11093751 Merrie}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  England did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh - I just came - I came home lik
e with all kinds of - uniform and kit bag and all - all the gear, different things I'd been issued with. What's all this? So I said, I've joined the Army. Well you can go and unjoin he said, the Army }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16450927\charrsid11093751 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16450927\charrsid11093751 you\rquote re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
 fifteen years of age. And then when he got down
 to brass tacks and saw that I had actually - actually enlisted and so on - he said, well, how old did you tell them you were? I said, eighteen. I said, you had to be eighteen. I said, when I first went in and - the recruiting sergeant I suppose you would
 
call him, he said to me, how old are you? I said, seventeen Sir. Well, he said, come back when you're eighteen. So as I'm going out the door somebody else said, just go out and come back and say you're eighteen, you know, like that's - they - they must sa
y that to you. So I went out then I turned on me heels and came back. And he said are you eighteen yet? I said, yes Sir. Right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 And you were in the Army then 'til when?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 I came out the first of July 1919.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 And you enjoyed your time in the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh no. Well I had a good time but - I went out very early. I left England in February 1915.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 You went over to France?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 No. I went out for the landing at the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10490510\charrsid11093751 Gallipoli}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10490510\charrsid11093751 I went to Egypt first where we were - kitted out, then I went - on a co
uple of islands in the Aegean Sea -Lemnos and Mudros if I remember right, I may be - that's going back such a long time sort of thing but - there was a - it's - I think they call it the Greek - the Greek - the Grecian Archipelago, there's a - quite a numb
er of islands clustered. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
And we were out there really sending them a postcard telling them we were on the way 'cos we were seeping only about - six or eight to a tent. Gleaming white canvas - the officers of course each had their own tent and - big white ma
rquees and - every day there were - two of the British big battleships used to come round and - fire at the Turkish ports and tour round. In other words we sent a postcard like we - like we're on our way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What did you find people were like in the Army - I think you said earlier that some of the young officers felt they were superior beings?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh yes. The - there was definitely - definitely a - quite a clash distinction. Yes. Very class conscious, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 More so than in civvy street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh yes. Yes. I found that more so in the Army than it was in - the civvy street, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 And how did you feel about that yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Well of course first I resented it then you had to - you had to absorb all that thing - a part of Arm - Army discipline.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 You didn't think about it a great deal then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 No. Even the - say a senior - you see, a Sergeant Major and that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16450927\charrsid11093751 business
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  - you - he insisted you called him sir. And you called other people by the rank. Corporal or sergeant or - you always had to give him his rank.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What jobs did you do after the first world war - I know you'd done quite a bit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
Oh - oh yes. Well everybody came - that came out of the Army - there were no jobs I mean everything was - was haywire you see, and - everybody I thi
n, almost without exception, went on the dole. Well - actually my firm, you know, Harrison Line, claimed me out, they could do that you see. If they guaranteed you a job when you got your discharge well you had to write to the firm and - say that - yes, a
nd they filled in the requisite form who they passed through various - places and eventually your dis - my discharge came through. You got in a month}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16450927\charrsid11093751 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 s leave and I'd only been out a week and I was wondering like where me money was coming from and - I went d
own to see them about a job and they wanted to know how soon could I start. I said, well I'm prepared to start any time you like. Could you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10490510\charrsid11093751 start}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  on Monday? I said, yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10490510\charrsid11093751 I started on Monday and they gave me the offer of a couple of - different jobs but the
 job that - that suited me best was getting down - after reporting to the office first thing in the morning - looking out for - short shipments, and what missed our boats, K.J. Harrison's they - they had a working arrangement with the Leyland Line that it
 was rushed up to their quay and put on their next ship you see because they worked shop for ship, you know, line for line. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
And - this often - necessitated the altering of - cargo - case numbers and , you know, markings on cases you see. And you also endeav
oured to stop all the short shipments you see. Suppose you'd got - fifty cases of Singer sewing machines - and - only - well say fifty cases of sewing machines now - right up to just on the closing date only thirty cases had actually arrived on the quaysi
de. They wouldn't be shipped until you got your full fifty there and then we found - I found out by going to railway companies of the various goods stations along the line of docks that - I'm - I'm going to be so many cases short. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10490510\charrsid11093751 Right, well I'd give - you
 would take the others up - up to Leylands Quay then you see and then get these - until these other cases came along and then some cases it meant 'em being - re - numbered and - so on.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 How long would you have been doing that for with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Well 
I was o - at the end of the first week, I called in the office on the Friday morning to pick up some papers and the cashier said, don't you want any money? I said, yes, why? Not appreciating the fact that the Friday was the pay day kind of thing, I hadn't
 
- got back into things. I said, yes. And - he offered me fifteen shillings a week. He offered - you know, sign here. I said, what part of the week does this represent? Called him by name and - he said, that's a full week Jimmy, here you are, I'll show you
 the paper. Mr Owen will re-start from the Army after the war, you know, wages fifteen shillings a week. So, I said, oh, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10490510\charrsid11093751 well}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
 I'm afraid that isn't any good to me. Well, he said, that's my instructions from Mr Lovatt, the manager. Would you like me to see him for you? I said, no, don't bother Mr D}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16450927\charrsid11093751 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
lton thanks, I said, I'll go and see him. So I - bearded Mr - Mr Robinson, his - his den and I said, excuse me Sir, I said, I've just been up for - up for my wages and, I said, Mr Dalton tells me fifteen shillings 
a week. He said, yes, that is right William. And your dinners of course - or luncheon vouchers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 So you slapped butter in the Maypole?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Slapped butter in the Maypole. At two pounds ten a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Why the wage difference then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Well - the wh
ite collar worker was always paid under the odds. By and large. Very poorly paid was a clerk. That's where you get the expression a tuppence ha'penny clerk. You see, they wouldn't belong to - I'm not a Communist, don't get me wrong - but they wouldn't bel
ong to any, you know, union or organisation. There was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16450927\charrsid11093751 C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 lerks Association which }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16450927\charrsid11093751 was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  a - more of a myth - it was just fin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16450927\charrsid11093751 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 ing jobs for certain people or they might find you jobs at a very low paid price. White collar workers now get very poorly paid. In - 
in the main, yes, compared to a tradesman. They have a temporary clerk in the Civil Service at this particular day and time, he's getting about twelve pounds a week gross. Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10490510\charrsid11093751 
Good gracious - a dustman gets far more than that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What then - who wants to be 
a dustman? It's a most invidious job - I mean, I've - I've been in charge of bin men and all this kind of thing - in charge of a depot - they come in, they smell. You can get bad - you know, leaky bins from people - people do kiddies on a plate and put it
 in the dustbin and all that - it's common practice. And there's - all kinds of offensive stuff is put in bin which - which should never go in a bin. Well what can you do.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What did you do from there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh went to work - for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10490510\charrsid11093751 Milner's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 , the safe works. I got a bit more money there but you worked very had and - and then - from there I went to - I went to Harland and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10490510\charrsid11093751 Wolfe's}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  and I got a job as a commissionaire - as a gatehouse keeper, like a commissionaire on the gate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Was the money better there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh the money was good 'cos I was working - I working twelve hours a day for seven day a week. Yes. And I had to get to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10490510\charrsid11093751 Bootle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  to start at six in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 A long way to go wasn't it in this area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Yes. But I was earning very good money th
ere because you were paid by the hour you see and I was doing an eighty-four hour week. Which included Saturday and Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What did you do after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh I was earning very good money then - about - in the rough I got about eight pound a week that is good. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What did you do after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
Well - I'd got into the - I got into the - time and cost office by that time you know, I worked myself into there and - I was working as a time keeper come cash clerk, you see, you done so many weeks
 in the main office then - so much down at the dock as a time keeper, you're all grouped together. They'd have the joiners, the platers - the this - all the different trades and there's a - a timekeeper for each - or a couple of timekeepers for each accor
d
ing to the number that you have. And you worked so many days out - outside and by working inside and outside and then I'd go inside for perhaps fourteen weeks or twelve weeks or eight weeks just as the case may be. Supply and demand kind of business. And 
so that - so that you - the outside man - knew what the inside - but knew, you know, knew just what information would be wanted inside and - and that business. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 And after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Well, after that - the joiners strike came on which put - after a
 couple of weeks we all got given an additional week's holiday with pay and then we came back and we were all put on the dole. I got five - I got me dole money which was still about fifteen bob a week plus five pounds from the firm. And - I think it was f
i
ve pound from the firm but anyway I - I - either three or five pound, I wouldn't be sure now. So - I wasn't so badly off. But when I went to the Labour Exchange one day to - to sign on - after a couple of weeks - two or three weeks - when I want to sign o
n
 I was given a card to go to the corporation, sit for an examination. And they said that they wanted time keepers come stock keepers cum various things and I went an sat for an exam. And - I took it and I was posted to the corporation at the housing depot
. AND I was there for forty-one years. Yes. And the money was rather poor but - you'd got the - you'd got the consolation of knowing that you'd got a job for life providing you kept your nose clean you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 And you worked your way up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 And you - 
yes. I think I actually started about - yes - I think I actually started at about - I think it was three fifteen - no, I got more than that. There was a bonus - I think the whole lot come to about - about four to - four pound five or something a week. Som
ething in that - line.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 But it was a regular sure job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh yes. And then after - after I'd been there - you done the twelve months - a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10490510\charrsid11093751 probationary}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  periods. And - provided there was a - there was a vacancy - someone had retired or died or something
 else and you kind of stepped up in seniority and I'd been there about twelve - eighteen months and - I was appointed as a timekeeper - storekeeper and then you started to go up. You go - like you're on a ladder. You're on the lowest - leg of the ladder b
ut you start to go up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Would you have preferred another type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 No, I was very satisfied, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did you serve an apprenticeship or training period for any of your jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 No. No, no, you picked it up as you went along, you jus
t - common sense and - being able to talk the language of the men or the bosses as required. Yes. I found that adaptability was the finest thing throughout.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did you belong to any trade union or professional organization?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 We were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16450927\charrsid11093751 mun}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  - well, firs
t of all we belonged to - oh what did they call it then - the - the Municipal Officers guild which was - it isn't a union kind of - and afterwards they were absorbed by N.A.L.G.O. - that's the National Association of Local Government Officers. And - then 
after a lot of people - didn't agree, like they would }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10490510\charrsid11093751 affiliate}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
 with the T.U.C. and all this kind of thing went on and you still went on paying your fees and they didn't appear to do anything where we found that the unions were doing a lot for the men and -
 quite a body of us broke away and we joined the - the General and Municipal Workers - the union - the - the chap that was Lord Bird at the time was the - was the earlier secretary, that was Frank Kane, lived in - lived in Aigburth - just station park lan
e - I forget the name of the road now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did you take part in any of the trade union activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
Well M have served on the committees but - I never had any pretences to - taking it up as a - well I - if you follow what I mean I - I did a - say the 
timekeepers rec. but these were only, you know, honorary jobs and I wouldn't think of taking on a - on a paid person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or different ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Well of course in the corporation you were - 
you always had to have the ratepayers interest at heart as well as - having the men's interests at heart. And - yes - and of course we got a lot of - a big lot of government subsidized work and - we had a most }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10490510\charrsid11093751 peculiar}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  - collection of men. You see, they we
re doing - people that were on the parish as we called it in those days - they were made to do test work from time to time. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10490510\charrsid11093751 
And - some of them never had - you know - had no proper food for a long, long time and this business and they used to more or less b
reak up at the pocket in the bad weather when we were doing these outside jobs such as - you know, Marrell Avenue, that was cut right through the fields - Spring wood Avenue - Menlow Avenue. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
Menlowe and Marrell Avenue - Speke Road, Garston and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did you feel there were divisions of interest among workers themselves?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh I don't know - I don't know how to answer that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did they have different aspirations and different ideas amongst themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh well, some did I suppose. You see
, you always get this - kind of - Communistic element in some places, now I'll tell you what I did find out but in different depots, this Orange versus Catholic - inter - dt was very strong in corporation depots, yes. Some yards were known as R.C. depots 
where they get R.C. bosses. And others were just the reverse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 This was still very strong then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
It's still alive in Liverpool now. At certain depots. Oh yes, it's very strong. If you get round - well of course I've been finished ten years but - ro
und at the south end of Liverpool I find that - the Protestants, and in Garston - I found that the Protestants was very strong kind of thing. Now for instance I wouldn't tell anyone in the Corporation that I was an R.C. Actually I wasn't an R.C. at heart 
but I wouldn't - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Some people say that in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh yes, there is. Yes, oh aye. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 No. I can - I think I can safely say that I've always enjoyed my - my work - and my home life. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did you continue to live at home after you left school when you were with the shipping firm for the first two years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh yes. Just my father. And - and this young sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your sister and your father at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 You had the same relationship with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did you spend your Sunday any differently when you left school and started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Well - yes, of course, I could - I could go out and join the boys, go to the park and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did you go to Sunday school and attend church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh no, no, no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10490510\charrsid11093751 Well - as a matter of fact we did attend chu
rch a bit because it was part and parcel of the football team that we went to St Anne's church Aigburth but had we not - I'm afraid always said as the Vicar would have - preach over the team kind of thing, do you follow what I mean?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did you take an interest in politics when you were a young man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Not at all in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Well - depends what you mean by young. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10490510\charrsid11093751 Not till}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  I'd been married quite a while, then of course it became part of your job to - well for instance you had to - 
you had to oppose them. We'd got - we have a chap now that's an M.P. in Parliament - possibly I shouldn't mention names but I - I will - Olrit. Now he would come along and say that he wanted to address the men in the cookhouse. I'd say right, between twel
v
e and one if they'll put up with you it's all yours but I want you to understand at one o'clock they're booking on again and going to work. Oh that's all right, he'd say. And he'd get in the cookhouse and he was of the type you'll have to do this and we s
a
y this and we say - well at one o'clock he'd blow them up and he'd possibly say, I'm just coming to the end of this Mr Owen. Say, well son, or Mr whatever it was - I said, twelve to one now, it's p- one o'clock, they're starting work. And I used to put 'e
m
 - and two or three times he - he hasn't kind of threatened me outright but it's been very much of a veiled threat. And I said, you can take it where the hell you like Sir - I'm not interested - I'm working for the corporation not for the union. I've noth
ing against you but I told you one o'clock is the deadline and they've got to work.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 You told me earlier how you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10490510\charrsid11093751 spent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  your spare time while you were at school - playing football and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did you continue to spend your spare time in the same way as a young working man or did you do different things now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10490510\charrsid11093751 
Well - actually by the time you got home from work - we'd finish at five thirty - five - five thirty somewhere around that time and by the time - yes - by the time I 
got - I got home - it was an hour after - that was six-thirty - when you had a meal and a clean up and you going to go out somewhere the time was pretty well on because - I always kept good hours, in fact - dad was a bit - you had to be in at ten like tha
t was a - an absolute deadline despite the fat that you're working. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
He put the bolt on the front door and he'd answer the door when you come and say, now I told you ten o'clock. Well dad this - all right - go this time but - think on - don't do it again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 What did you do in the evening if you did go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh we played at the tennis field and - you often }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10490510\charrsid11093751 fagged}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751  out, got a tanner for it and - things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Who would your friends have been then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Just the local lads.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did you make any new friends when you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh yes, yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10490510\charrsid11093751 
Well I made friends there you see, we - we'd got to make them you see and it was starting a new life and fortunately I knew two or three through either playing football or - there was the - the chief p
ark keeper's son - fellow named Patterson, we used to go to work together 'cos he worked at the dock office and I worked at T.J's and - I - I knew Frank Patterson through playing football with him and that and - like we'd go together and of course then - 
then we met other people. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 
Now there was the Peoples Hall in Aigburth - I think you know the Peoples Hall do you? Well they had a gymnasium down below - they'd got billiard table upstairs and you got that - and we didn't sup beer but you could always get cup
s of tea and things like that and we used to play see for four cups of tea, it was only a penny a cup.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did you have any girl friends then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh well - I think I was fifteen when I first - well, I tell we used to go to the Pavilion, two of us with 
two girls, two sisters. There was nothing to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 How did you meet the girls - were they girls in the neighbourhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 No, I think they were two girls we'd - we just met in the park you know. Nothing to it at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did you bring friends home at that stage in your life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 A couple of boy friends sometimes, yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Never girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh good gracious, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Did your father expect to know where you were when you went out in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 He might ask me anything - you know, where have you been like -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Would he expect to be told before you went out where you were going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh no, I'd say if I was going anywhere special. Otherwise he'd know I was just in the neighbourhood you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8157651 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 And you had to be home by ten o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14963447 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid864932\charrsid11093751 Oh that was an absolute deadline.
\par }}